  <thing id="deiAureon" name="Aureon" description="A deity of lore and magic.  Aureon is lawful neutral.  The patron of all arcane spellcasters, as well as sages, librarians and scribes, he appears as a gnome or human, wizard in ancient texts, and occassionally as a majestic blue dragon.  He is the brother of Onatar, the husband of Boldrei, and strangely related to the Shadow.  Associated with the Domains of Knowledge, Law, and Magic.   Aureon&apos;s favored weapon is the quarterstaff." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="God of Law and Knowledge"/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="Law, knowledge, learning, logic, magic."/>
    <fieldval field="deiCentWor" value="Shrines to Aureon are normally stone and contain many carvings that support the acquisition of knowledge, such as historical murals. All contain a library of some sort, even if the community can manage no more than a table strewn with a handful of books or parchments."/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value="An open tome, or the Octogram in shades of black and white, representing both ink on paper and the s"/>
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
