  <thing id="deiBalinor" name="Balinor" description="A neutral nature deity associated with hunting and animal life, Balinor claims hunters, druids, barbarians and rangers among his followers, since he appears as both a protector of nature and an exemplar of gently taking what one needs for sustenance from nature&apos;s bounty.  Usually portrayed as a burly human, sometimes as a crude but good-natured half-orc, and occassionally as a stalking green dragon, he is brother to Arawai and the Devourer.  Associated with the domains of Air, Animal and Earth.  Balinor&apos;s favored weapon is the battleaxe." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="God of Beasts and the Hunt"/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="Animals, the hunt."/>
    <fieldval field="deiCentWor" value="Balinor’s shrines are constructed of wood, often covered in furs or greenery to better blend into the background. A temple is rarely found within a town, although it might be only a few minutes’ walk away."/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value="A silhouetted pair of antlers, or the Octogram in brown and red, representing the flesh, blood, and "/>
