  <thing id="deiBoldrei" name="Boldrei" description="Boldrei, the lawful good deity of community, is invoked as a protector of villages and homes, to bless marriages, and to confirm government appointments.  Usually depicted in ancient texts as a commoner of any race, or sometimes as a copper dragon brooding over a nest of eggs, she is Aureon&apos;s wife.  The domains under her influence are Community, Good, Law and Protection.  Boldrei&apos;s favored weapon is the spear." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="Goddess of Community and Hearth"/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="Hearth, community, marriage, government."/>
    <fieldval field="deiCentWor" value="Boldrei’s shrines appear very homey and might even be mistaken for cottages. They are adorned and furnished for comfort, to remind worshipers that she is the patron of the home."/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value="A fire in a stone hearth, or the Octogram in orange and gray, representing fire and stone."/>
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
