  <thing id="deiKolKorn" name="Kol Korran" description="Merchants, traders, and thieves revere Kol Korran, the neutral deity of trade and money-as might anyone who has money or wants more.  He is depicted as a fat, cheerful human or dwarf in fine clothes.  A few ancient representations of him show a white dragon lying on a bed of ice-blue gemstones.  Said to be the son of Olladra and Onatar and the twin brother of the Keeper, he oversees the domains of Charm, Commerce, and Travel.  Kol Korran&apos;s favored weapon is the mace." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="God of Trade and Wealth"/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="Wealth, money, trade, commerce, theft."/>
    <fieldval field="deiCentWor" value="Kol Korran’s temples might be of stone or wood, but they always use the best available materials. The most opulent are decorated in tapestries and silks of gold and silver. Those in the poorest communities sport the greatest riches that can be spared, and are painted to appear as though they contain more than they do."/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value="A nine-sided gold coin stamped with the Octogram, or the Octogram in gold and silver, representing t"/>
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
