  <thing id="deiDevoure" name="Devourer, The" description="The brother of Arawai and Balinor, the Devourer is neutral evil.  Stories say that he raped his sister Araway and thereby fathered the Fury.  As lord of the deep waters and  master of maulstrom and reef, he represents all the destructive power of nature.  The sahuagin worship him, while sailers fear him and seek to appease him.  He is portrayed as a human or merfolk with seaweed in his hair and beard, as a sahuagin, as an enormous shark, or as a dragon turtle.  The domains associated with him are Destruction, Evil, Water, and Weather.  The Devourer&apos;s favored weapon is the trident." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="God of Destruction and the Sea."/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="Devastation, hunger, nautical travel, storms, water."/>
    <fieldval field="deiCentWor" value="Shrines to the Devourer are usually built of wood, and many are roofless, allowing rain to enter freely. Others are built on the water itself, either on lakeside barges or in the cabins of seafaring vessels. They stink of blood and are hung with rotting seaweed."/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value="A bundle of five sharpened bones."/>
    <usesource source="srcFaOfEb"/>
