  <thing id="deiTravele" name="Traveler, The" description="The most mysterious of the Dark Six, the Traveler is chaotic neutral and seems to have no connection to the other deities of the pantheon.  A consummate shapeshifter, the Traveller is said to walk the land in a thousand disguises.  A master of cunning and deception, it emphasizes subtlety and careful planning.  In some places the Traveler is known as the Giver of Gifts, but proverbs warn, &quot;Beware the gifts of the Traveler.&quot;  Revered by doppelgangers, lycanthropes, and a number of changelings and shifters, it is associated with the domains of Artifice, Chaos, Travel, and Trickery.  The Traveler&apos;s favored weapon is the scimitar." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
    <fieldval field="deiEpithet" value="God of Trickery and Gifts."/>
    <fieldval field="deiPortfol" value="Chaos, deception, evolution, invention, transformation."/>
    <fieldval field="deiCentWor" value="Shrines to the Traveler have no consistent make or design. Each worshiper is expected to create a personal place of worship and to alter it regularly."/>
    <fieldval field="deiSymbol" value=" An eight-pointed configuration of four crossed and rune-inscribed bones."/>
